TITLE: CS:S Map - de_DomesticDispute
AUTHOR: SM Sith Lord
E-MAIL: smsithlord@yahoo.com
WEBSITE: http://www.sithmercenaries.net

FILENAME: de_DomesticDispute.bsp
FILESIZE: 14.3 MB
DATE RELEASED: Semptember 9th, 2006

CREDITS: All the beta testers, including SmokeDawg, Beefcaike, Grrnnaawwlwl, Master Yoda, SM Nesseight,
SM GrimR3, SM Mister Moe. And the servers who hosted my beta for play testing, NoobsRUs (OldSkool)
and NKM (NKM PorkChop).

DESCRIPTION: CT's camp the house, T's bomb the house. The upstairs panic room unlocks after 1 minute
of gameplay so the CT's can rescue the single hostage incase the Terrorists are not doing their job.

BUGS: Nav mesh still isn't perfect, and bots can still see thru some objects they shouldn't.


Terrorists Objectives:
The local anti-terrorist unit has foiled a fund-raising mission of one of our urban cells. They have
barricaded themselvs in our brothers' own safehouse and are performing an on-site interogation. You
have been air lifted to immediately radicate the situation.

Objective A - Do not allow ANY compromised information leave the scene, AT ALL COSTS. (hostage)
Objective B - Destroy all evidence linking us to our fallen cell. (bombs)


Counter-Terrorists Objectives:
After foiling a local terrorist plot, a high speed chase has ended at what appears to be the terrorist
safehouse. Following a brief fire fight, we have secured the premesis. An FBI offical has already
appeard on the scene to conduct an emergency on-site interogation of the two survivors. He has informed
us that the suspects are only a small cell in a major, international terrorisim organization and
additional terrorist forces may very well be enroute. For this reason, he will conduct his interogation
in the terrorist's own panic room until back-up can arrive.

Objective A - Protect ALL evidence in the terrorist safehouse. (guard bombsites)
Objective B - Ensure the completion of the FBI interogation. (guard panic room)
Objective C - Escort FBI official to safety upon completion of his interogation. (hostage)

My second map after de_site23 http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/109619.

I set this at night in a sort of dystopian city district, with strong lighting and a cyber punk feel I guess. The rain in the map adds to the atmosphere. The layout is similar to dust2 in scale and structure. All files are zipped into the bsp. Supports up to 32 players. Some people may not like the darker maps but turn your brightness up if you're having problems, it's fine on my machine but if you have brightness low it may look dark. Its part of the atmosphere in my opinion but im sure some people will still trash because enemies arent as clear to see.

This is the first version I have released, having done some testing with friends. One issue that has arose is that the rain is not rendering properly on some peoples PC. The rain looks fine on my PC with the default settings (see screenshots). However, having tested it on some other PCs, the rain seems to be rendering very bright white which spoils the look completely. It is easy to fix with the 'r_rainalpha' console command but this requires cheats to be enabled. If anyone is having this problem and knows how to fix this I would love the feedback as its very frustrating when people don't see the map at its best. No idea why it renders different on some peoples machines and not others.

Anyway, enjoy and feel free to distribute. Many thanks if I have used your art on one of the billboards, i'm not an artist and I wanted to add some flair to the map and had to use pics are found for free. I'm sorry if I've accidentely used something I shouldn't have, I did try to check.

Although this map is based on the MW2 map "Skidrow," I made it all from memory, did not look at the actual map at all for like a year.  Worked hard on this for 3 days to get accustomed to hammer again after a long break :D

Basic fun map, smash the square cubes to send others to their deaths or use standard weapons to kill them. The intention is for terrorists to plant the bomb at the bombsite floating underneath the arena by rushing it from their base and counter-terrorists defend. Game follows the basic principles of glasstrap, but with neon lighting (beware of strobe effect) and a bombsite.

BOTs not supported, they get stuck at the spawn area.

New things in the map:

-new camping place
-flowers you can walk through
-playerclip

have fun!
